article.headline: Portland State 68, Montana State 51
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Seamus Boxley scored 22 points to lead Portland State to a 68-51 victory over Montana State on Saturday night. The win put the Vikings (14-6, 6-2 league) in sole possession of first place in the Big Sky Conference. Antone Jarrell added 11 points for the Vikings and Tyler Hollist had nine points on 3-of-8 shooting from beyond the 3-point line. Marvin Moss led Montana State (10-10, 5-2) with 18 points and was the only Bobcat to reach double figures. After falling behind 15-6 midway through the first half, the Vikings found their offensive flow, hitting three 3-pointers during a 16-2 run to grab a 26-18 lead with 3:36 left in the half. A 10-3 second-half run, capped by an off-the-backboard alley-oop from Will Funn to Blake Walker, put the Vikings up 46-36 with 10:22 left. They were in control the rest of the way. The Vikings struggled early from the field but managed to shoot 43 percent from the floor. They limited Montana State to 34 percent.
